SUMMARY:Easter Monday Hike! Hilton Fallsss
DESCRIPTION:These Boots Are Made for Hiking\n**Meetup point: Corner of Ten
  Side Rd and Fourth Line Nassagaweya**\n(Nearest googable address to : 101
 25 Fourth Line Nassagaweya\, Campbellville\, ON L0P 1B0)\n\nHilton Falls C
 onservation is a hidden gem you don't want to miss.\nThe trail experience 
 here is spectacular\, with most people giving this loop a solid five-stars
 . There is lots of variety in the environment\, and you will pass through 
 forests\, streams\, peaceful nooks\, meadows\, wetlands\, over ridges\, an
 d some muddy sections. After passing the initial part of the hike that fol
 lows flat trails\, you will also take a thinner Bruce Side Trail which is 
 a more similar experience to hiking in the Bruce Peninsula. Then you will 
 come along to the Falls\, and you can travel down by the pond. Then\, you 
 will take another side trail through some swampy terrain. Though folks rec
 ommend hiking in summer\, winter is an exceptional experience since you ge
 t to see the frozen falls via snowshoes.\n\nProper foot wear is required!
